components.title: Just Dance Minute - Just Dance 2017 Cosplays
components.description: Just Dance Ambassador UbiMouss gives a shoutout to the best Just Dance 2017 cosplays so far!
components.subtitles:
1
00:00:06,230 --> 00:00:07,470
Hey Just Dancers !

2
00:00:07,470 --> 00:00:10,360
I’m UbiMouss and this is Just Dance Minute !

3
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:12,250
Oh, that?

4
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:15,600
This is just something that I picked out of
my wardrobe

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:21,240
Because yeah: a special Just Dance Minute
deserves a special outfit…

6
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:26,410
Just Dance 2017 has been out for less than
a month but I am already proclaiming that

7
00:00:26,410 --> 00:00:27,410
we’ve had the

8
00:00:27,410 --> 00:00:28,410
BEST.

9
00:00:28,410 --> 00:00:29,410
COSPLAYS.

10
00:00:29,410 --> 00:00:30,410
EVER.

11
00:00:30,410 --> 00:00:33,670
You guys have been so creative in the last
months that I felt the need to give a huge

12
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:39,570
shoutout to all of you great cosplayers who
are making so many amazing Just Dance 2017

13
00:00:39,570 --> 00:00:40,570
costumes.

14
00:00:40,570 --> 00:00:45,149
First one: Luis from Brazil, who I think was
the first one to share photos of the making

15
00:00:45,149 --> 00:00:49,199
of his costume for one of the coaches of Lean
On last July.

16
00:00:49,199 --> 00:00:51,430
So bravo to him!

17
00:00:51,430 --> 00:00:57,620
Then comes a new Just Dancer in the family:
Jakov Petrowsky from France with the same

18
00:00:57,620 --> 00:00:58,899
coach of Lean On.

19
00:00:58,899 --> 00:01:01,129
Yeah this coach is pretty cool.

20
00:01:01,129 --> 00:01:06,800
He spent a lot of time working on the hair
too and for that deserves a 10/10.

21
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:11,830
Next up: Melissa Salvatore from Russia, who
already blew our minds last year with her

22
00:01:11,830 --> 00:01:13,380
cosplay of Albatraoz.

23
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:19,500
She’s back this year with her cosplay of
Worth It, and hopefully this is not the last

24
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:20,500
one!

25
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:24,380
Another Worth It cosplay but from Nijishoujo
from New-York this time.

26
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:29,770
An amazing rendition of the costume, that
she have been dancing with during her streams

27
00:01:29,770 --> 00:01:30,770
on Twitch.

28
00:01:30,770 --> 00:01:33,940
You can follow her: link in the description.

29
00:01:33,940 --> 00:01:39,320
She also created her own version of the “Run
The Night” coach and we just love it.

30
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:44,990
And last but not least today: Nikita from
Russia, and his own version of the “Don’t

31
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:46,700
Stop Me Now” coach.

32
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:49,610
Almost identical to the in-game version.

33
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:54,200
Many thanks to all of you guys for these amazing
creations and keep sharing those with us!

34
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:57,550
It’ll be my pleasure to send goodies to
the best ones.

35
00:01:57,550 --> 00:02:01,590
This Just Dance Minute is over so see you
soon and until then: Just Dance!
